## 4. Frontend Architecture Standards

### 4.1 Required Imports (All Pages)

```typescript
import { resolveMediaSrc } from '@/lib/apiBase';  // ✅ Images
import { formatDrfErrorPayload, isAxiosError } from '@/lib/drfErrors';  // ✅ Errors
import { pageLogger } from '@/lib/logger';  // ✅ Logging
```

### 4.2 Required Imports (All Composables)

```typescript
import { formatDrfErrorPayload, isAxiosError } from '@/lib/drfErrors';  // ✅ Errors
import { entityLogger } from '@/lib/logger';  // ✅ Logging
```

### 4.3 Page Component Structure

Use template at: `bipflow-frontend/src/templates/PERFECT_PAGE.TEMPLATE.vue`

Key sections:
1. State machine (forms, modals)
2. Data layer (composables)
3. Async operation states
4. Computed properties
5. Event handlers (CRUD)
6. Lifecycle

### 4.4 Composable Structure

Use template at: `bipflow-frontend/src/templates/useEntity.TEMPLATE.ts`

Key sections:
1. Module-level singleton store
2. Error handling helpers
3. CRUD operations (fetch, create, update, delete)
4. Payload preparation
5. Public API (return object)

### 4.5 Image Rendering

```vue
<script setup lang="ts">
import { resolveMediaSrc } from '@/lib/apiBase';

const imageUrl = computed(() =>
  product.value.image ? resolveMediaSrc(product.value.image) : null
);
</script>

<template>
  <!-- ✅ Images always use resolveMediaSrc -->
  <img :src="imageUrl" alt="Product" />
</template>
```

### 4.6 List Rendering

```vue
<template>
  <!-- ✅ MUST include updated_at in key for cache invalidation -->
  <div
    v-for="item in items"
    :key="`${item.id}-${item.updated_at}`"
    class="item-card"
  >
    <!-- Content -->
  </div>
</template>
```

