## 7. Code Quality Checklist

When you generate or review code, verify:

- [ ] Vue components use `<script setup lang="ts">` only
- [ ] Images use `resolveMediaSrc()` helper
- [ ] Errors use `formatDrfErrorPayload()`
- [ ] List items have `:key="{id}-{updated_at}"`
- [ ] Updates use PATCH (never PUT)
- [ ] Creates use POST
- [ ] Composables are singletons (module-level state)
- [ ] Models include `created_at` and `updated_at`
- [ ] Serializers export timestamps as read-only
- [ ] ViewSets have `permission_classes`
- [ ] All required imports present
- [ ] Error states properly handled

